The generalized incidence rate function more accurately describes the changes in transmission caused by factors such as population size, behavioral changes, and asymptomatic individuals. In particular, asymptomatic individuals play an important role in transmission, which traditional linear models fail to capture effectively. By adjusting the transmission rates, the model can effectively simulate the effects of medical interventions and social distancing measures. By numerically simulating the adjustments of parameters \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
